    <section id="projects">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Featured Projects</h2>
            <div class="project-grid">
                
                <article class="project-card">
                    <span class="impact-badge">$2B Annual Revenue Impact</span>
                    <h3>Video on Facebook for iPad</h3>
                    
                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>The Challenge</h4>
                        <p>While mobile video experiences evolved rapidly, the iPad was overlooked, leading to significant content cropping issues[cite: 12, 15]. Media was set to fill the screen width, causing advertiser content to be cut off—a major revenue loss for the company[cite: 16, 23].</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>My Role & Strategy</h4>
                        <p>I led this project from conception to MVP launch[cite: 8]. I conducted an audit and competitive analysis of TikTok and YouTube Shorts to determine how to leverage the iPad's larger surface area[cite: 29, 33].</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Designed a "Northstar" vision featuring blurred previews ("peeking"), color-sampled backgrounds, and UI moved off-media to maximize engagement[cite: 73, 77, 79].</li>
                            <li>Balanced engineering constraints by shipping an MVP that anchored UI to the bottom of the screen, ensuring a consistent scrolling experience regardless of content shape[cite: 85, 94].</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>Success Metrics</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Generated <strong>$89M bi-weekly revenue increase</strong> ($2B annually)[cite: 103].</li>
                            <li>Increased <strong>total watch time by 1.5%</strong> and Daily Active Users (DAU) by 0.74%[cite: 104].</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="project-card">
                    <span class="impact-badge">Targeting Q1 2026 Launch</span>
                    <h3>Location in AI Mode (Google)</h3>
                    
                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>The Problem</h4>
                        <p>Google's experimental Gemini-powered "AI Mode" (AIM) launched without the robust location controls found in classical Search[cite: 105, 106]. Users with poor location data were 5.7% more likely to abandon AIM for regular Search[cite: 111].</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>The Solution</h4>
                        <p>I am leading the design effort to integrate durable location affordances directly into the conversational flow[cite: 107, 116].</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Developed a centralized location "hub" that combines a location picker with transparency about how data is sourced[cite: 146, 147].</li>
                            <li>Designed a "multiple locations" solution for queries like "pizza in NY and NJ," allowing users to create custom geographic boundaries[cite: 213, 216].</li>
                            <li>Implemented prominent prompts for Device Location (DL) to provide the most durable fix for future queries[cite: 198, 199].</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>Impact</h4>
                        <p>The project has received leadership approval and is currently being built by engineering for a Q1 2026 launch[cite: 223].</p>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="project-card">
                    <span class="impact-badge">+173% Increase in CTR</span>
                    <h3>iCloud Private Relay</h3>
                    
                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>The Context</h4>
                        <p>Apple's iCloud Private Relay (iPR) obscures IP addresses, causing Google Search to return irrelevant results (e.g., showing a user in New Hampshire results for Ohio)[cite: 235, 238].</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>My Solution</h4>
                        <p>I designed a callout card to inform users of potential inaccuracies and provide a direct path to "Use precise location"[cite: 232]. I tested multiple content variants to find the most effective messaging.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project-section">
                        <h4>Results</h4>
                        <p>The solution increased the Click-Through Rate (CTR) for the "Use precise location" button from <strong>0.84% to 2.3%</strong>, a 173% improvement[cite: 234].</p>
                    </div>
                </article>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

